{
    "description": "Non-ESKAPE bacterial species for the 'Other' negative training class. Curated from NCBI reference genomes of clinically relevant bacteria spanning diverse phyla. Used to train the classifier to reject non-ESKAPE inputs.",
    "scope_rationale": "Selected from species with NCBI reference genomes that are commonly encountered in clinical microbiology labs (human pathogens, commensals, and environmental species frequently confused with pathogens). Spans Firmicutes, Gammaproteobacteria, Alphaproteobacteria, Betaproteobacteria, Actinobacteria, Bacteroidetes, Spirochaetes, and other phyla to maximise k-mer diversity.",
    "excluded": [
        "Enterococcus faecium",
        "Staphylococcus aureus",
        "Klebsiella pneumoniae",
        "Acinetobacter baumannii",
        "Pseudomonas aeruginosa",
        "Enterobacter cloacae"
    ],
